          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "194Pt target of thickness 265 ug/cm2 on 10 ug/cm2",
                "thick carbon backing"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two silicon detectors were used inside the",
                "target chamber, placed at an angle +- 22.7 degrees,",
                "to detect the elastically scattered particles and",
                "flux normalization."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The evaporation redidues reaching the focal",
                "plane were detected using a position sensitive",
                "multiwire proportional counter (MWPC) of active area",
                "15 x 5 cm2. This detector was operated with isobutane",
                "gas at 2 mbar pressure and it provided two-",
                "dimensional position (X, Y) signals, energy loss",
                "signal (cathode) and timing signal (anode)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fission measurements were performed",
                "in a separate experiment using the scattering chamber",
                "of BARC-TIFR 14UD Pelletron accelerator facility. The",
                "fission fragments were collected using three dE-E",
                "silicon detector telescopes consisting of 15.20 um",
                "thick dE detectors and 300.500 um thick E detectors.",
                "An aluminium collimator of diameter 5 mm was used in",
                "front of each telescope assembly. These telescopes",
                "were placed at 13.6 cm from the target, on the same",
                "movable arm of the scattering chamber."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two silicon surface barrier detectors were",
                "mounted at angle +- 20 degrees with respect to the",
                "beam direction, at a distance of 42 cm from the",
                "target center. The elastic events recorded in these",
                "detectors were used for the normalization of the",
                "fission yields and estimation of the absolute",
                "differential cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
